fectious agents or toxins. Committee functions are administrated through the Office of Animal Care and Institutional Biosafety (OACIB) within the Office of the Vice Chancellor for Research.The goal of the OACIB is to facilitate the protocol writing/review process for the investigator and to ensure compliance of rDNA and infectious agent research with federal regulations. OACIB accepts all protocol submissions, coordinates protocol review, notifies the investigator of the outcome of protocol review and works with investigators during the protocol writing/review process.Please contact us if you have questions regarding the use of rDNA and/or infectious agents or toxins in research.          rDNA & Infectious Agents (IBC)    Back to main content           Forms    Committee Composition & Expertise    Meeting & Deadlines    Policies & Guidelines    Education & Training    Online Resources    FAQs                   UIC Logo         Office Of  The Vice  Chancellor  For  Research                   Contact   Office of the Vice Chancellor for Research  1737 West Polk Street, Suite 310, MC 672, Chicago, IL 60612  Phone: (312) 996-4995  Fax: (312 ) 996-9598  ovcrweb@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  Â© 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 